Class DynamicDefinition

      • com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.business.SettableIdAuditableEntity<DynamicDefinition>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.business.Auditable<String>, com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.business.EntityWithDto<DynamicDefinition>, com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.business.IdBasedEntity, Serializable, Comparable<DynamicDefinition>, org.springframework.data.domain.Persistable<Long>

    @Entity
public class DynamicDefinition
extends com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.business.SettableIdAuditableEntity<DynamicDefinition>
implements Comparable<DynamicDefinition>
    Represents a definition of the template for a DynamicDocumentDefinition, DynamicTypeDefinition or a form. A definition holds the link to the latest DynamicDefinitionVersion for the definition it represents.

    Usually a DynamicDefinition is not linked directly, but rather through a DynamicDefinitionVersion to link to a specific version of a document definition.

    Since:
    0.0.1
    Author:
    Steven Gentens

        public DynamicDefinition getParent()
